#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:3 107bf68428d945d2a6488d58fce8cb4c
msgid "How to make any file persistent (bind-dirs)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:7 f77dc3d4739549b3a088376a1ecda9d0
msgid "This page is intended for advanced users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:10 a028c620fb6e48a681276c8997be5119
msgid "What are bind-dirs?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:13 a5381ba5a0a045c3a4467f51589d84f9
msgid ""
"With `bind-dirs <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-core-agent-"
"linux/blob/master/vm-systemd/bind-dirs.sh>`__ any arbitrary files or "
"folders can be made persistent in app qubes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:16 73a3d7f8a2b94c2ea5873723e85efc9b
msgid "What is it useful for?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:19 0f5bbe64b6fe4a219716ec65c696fea2
msgid ""
"In an app qube all of the file system comes from the template except "
"``/home``, ``/usr/local``, and ``/rw``. This means that changes in the "
"rest of the filesystem are lost when the app qube is shutdown. bind-dirs "
"provides a mechanism whereby files usually taken from the template can be"
" persisted across reboots."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:21 15f1444c4c3f40b18cc7685213694291
msgid ""
"For example, in Whonix, Tor’s data dir ``/var/lib/tor`` `has been made "
"persistent in the TemplateBased ProxyVM sys-whonix "
"<https://github.com/Whonix/qubes-"
"whonix/blob/8438d13d75822e9ea800b9eb6024063f476636ff/usr/lib/qubes-bind-"
"dirs.d/40_qubes-whonix.conf#L5>`__. In this way sys-whonix can benefit "
"from the Tor anonymity feature ‘persistent Tor entry guards’ but does not"
" have to be a standalone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:24 083fc84d27c9485db42001178d712154
msgid "How to use bind-dirs.sh?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:27 15349c2b2774480d86ea34aa9a7a1b4c
msgid ""
"In this example, we want to make ``/var/lib/tor`` persistent. Enter all "
"of the following commands in your app qube."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:29 7feae080c8094b3bb82bc2e55405ebdb
msgid "Make sure the directory ``/rw/config/qubes-bind-dirs.d`` exists."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:37 cacbffa32ed34e4c805e52c1149c93f4
msgid ""
"Create the file ``/rw/config/qubes-bind-dirs.d/50_user.conf`` with root "
"permissions, if it doesn’t already exist."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:45 50683f4253b243e0adeff824fcfad072
msgid ""
"Add a line to ``/rw/config/qubes-bind-dirs.d/50_user.conf`` that appends "
"a folder or file to the ``binds`` variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:53 07cd6369688044fea76313ddfed319b8
msgid "Save."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:55 8787484c5d7c4fe99160a4f8404b68ad
msgid ""
"If the directory you wish to make persistent doesn’t exist in the "
"template on which the app qube is based, you’ll need to create the "
"directory (with its full path) under ``/rw/bind-dirs`` in the app qube. "
"For example, if ``/var/lib/tor`` didn’t exist in the template, then you "
"would execute the following command in your app qube:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:63 81472c367b3e4e909bf01440072e6927
msgid ""
"(optional) If the directory you want to persist across reboots "
"(``/var/lib/tor`` in this case) needs special ownership and permissions, "
"make sure the directory you created just under ``/rw/bind-dirs/`` has the"
" same ones (using the commands ``chown`` and ``chmod``, respectively)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:65 91a9139bd5004b49bfe96dd72f928b94
msgid "Reboot the app qube."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:67 cdcd7fcb39274ec58743d9a667ecd2d2
msgid "Done."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:71 feec380aa73d44e8b42ce0c69b25e393
msgid ""
"From now on, all files in the ``/var/lib/tor`` directory will persist "
"across reboots."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:73 2f7b3d86e9384b0194e166dceb7c9208
msgid ""
"You can make as many files or folders persist as you want simply by "
"making multiple entries in the ``50_user.conf`` file, each on a separate "
"line. For example, if you added the file ``/etc/tor/torrc`` to the "
"``binds`` variable, any modifications to *that* file would also persist "
"across reboots."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:83 6f2e59ad39bf4df19e725a79e06fa3ba
msgid "Other Configuration Folders"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:86 f52f20c7e6bd4933868223f3c873ef55
msgid "``/usr/lib/qubes-bind-dirs.d`` (lowest priority, for packages)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:88 e4aadd9fea464003b987669d99cee93b
msgid ""
"``/etc/qubes-bind-dirs.d`` (intermediate priority, for template wide "
"configuration)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:90 419a90cf7f794eadbbc71e3e945e0edc
msgid ""
"``/rw/config/qubes-bind-dirs.d`` (highest priority, for per VM "
"configuration)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:95 5ab364ec9dd2445bbfc91c80d31daa13
msgid "How does it work?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:98 177a15cb498a46eba67f205e97799360
msgid ""
"bind-dirs.sh is called at startup of an app qube, and configuration files"
" in the above configuration folders are parsed to build a bash array. "
"Files or folders identified in the array are copied to ``/rw/bind-dirs`` "
"if they do not already exist there, and are then bind mounted over the "
"original files/folders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:100
#: 339fcccd3f7a42ca9619e54c9e3cfb41
msgid ""
"Creation of the files and folders in ``/rw/bind-dirs`` should be "
"automatic the first time the app qube is restarted after configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:102
#: 9e72a1397f424cc4b3958b02756cdbfa
msgid ""
"If you want to circumvent this process, you can create the relevant file "
"structure under ``/rw/bind-dirs`` and make any changes at the same time "
"that you perform the configuration, before reboot. Note that you must "
"create the full folder structure under ``/rw/bind-dirs`` - e.g you would "
"have to create ``/rw/bind-dirs/var/lib/tor``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:105
#: c799060404b4486c84737795ee66fe77
msgid "Limitations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:108
#: f2d0ec2695b5480b9c0456383f46c992
msgid ""
"Files that exist in the template root image cannot be deleted in the app "
"qubes root image using bind-dirs.sh."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:110
#: 28d1e982830d4c9bb4302120a6d60c67
msgid ""
"Re-running ``sudo /usr/lib/qubes/init/bind-dirs.sh`` without a previous "
"``sudo /usr/lib/qubes/init/bind-dirs.sh umount`` does not work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:112
#: 42e5deff189f48ccbd9a24638b4d6b47
msgid ""
"Running ``sudo /usr/lib/qubes/init/bind-dirs.sh umount`` after boot "
"(before shutdown) is probably not sane and nothing can be done about "
"that."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:114
#: e5586e62697a48e4873331cb8c8b76f0
msgid ""
"Many editors create a temporary file and copy it over the original file. "
"If you have bind mounted an individual file this will break the mount. "
"Any changes you make will not survive a reboot. If you think it likely "
"you will want to edit a file, then either include the parent directory in"
" bind-dirs rather than the file, or perform the file operation on the "
"file in ``/rw/bind-dirs``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:116
#: 3fbddf8796e24dd0b490793924b3bb16
msgid ""
"Some files are altered when a qube boots - e.g. ``/etc/hosts``. If you "
"try to use bind-dirs on such files you may break your qube in "
"unpredictable ways. You can add persistent rules to ``/etc/hosts`` using "
":doc:`/rw/config/rc.local </user/advanced-topics/config-files>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:121
#: 2cec2b1fec5c40bebe5f31cb4ae0be5d
msgid "How to remove binds from bind-dirs.sh?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:124
#: 7f3b341933e14ddbb7ff36e5a180b6b2
msgid ""
"``binds`` is actually just a bash variable (an array) and the bind-"
"dirs.sh configuration folders are sourced as bash snippets in lexical "
"order. Therefore if you wanted to remove an existing entry from the "
"``binds`` array, you could do that by using a lexically higher "
"configuration file. For example, if you wanted to make ``/var/lib/tor`` "
"non-persistent in ``sys-whonix`` without manually editing ``/usr/lib"
"/qubes-bind-dirs.d/40_qubes-whonix.conf``, you could use the following "
"in:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:126
#: bd4f310e7b1a401da6ec65ecdfccf2fa
msgid "``/rw/config/qubes-bind-dirs.d/50_user.conf``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:134
#: 5fadac8142e342409593c0a01a7de1be
msgid ""
"(Editing ``/usr/lib/qubes-bind-dirs.d/40_qubes-whonix.conf`` directly is "
"strongly discouraged, since such changes get lost when that file is "
"changed in the package on upgrades.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:137
#: a313018e4a214bbd905715fcbb8c89ee
msgid "Custom persist feature"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:140
#: 4e4846b167f04e64a3f3b9aded4b948d
msgid ""
"Custom persist is an optional advanced feature allowing the creation of "
"minimal state AppVM. The purpose of such an AppVM is to avoid unwanted "
"data to persist as much as possible by disabling the ability to configure"
" persistence from the VM itself. When enabled, the following happens:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:142
#: 0e5b97ad200246808d3396f3e15a92b5
msgid "``/rw/config/rc.local`` is no longer executed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:144
#: e46258f53e404f158d58139d7440dc34
msgid "``/rw/config/qubes-firewall-user-script`` is ignored"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:146
#: eef4f84a5b954e6884bce4da9b1a4594
msgid "``/rw/config/suspend-module-blacklist`` is ignored"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:148
#: 18d9a224f97346658d3919011a6a3100
msgid ""
"User bind dirs defined in ``/rw/config/qubes-bind-dirs.d`` are no longer "
"read"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:150
#: 23e711aec0694de2b49af0ca89939ee6
msgid ""
"``/home`` and ``/user/local`` are not persistent anymore unless "
"explicitly configured."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:154
#: 6ef4ad493b184775a9c8f45cc5005988
msgid ""
"Bind dirs are obviously still supported but this must be configured "
"either in the template (``/usr/lib/qubes-bind-dirs.d`` and ``/etc/qubes-"
"bind-dirs.d``) or from dom0 using ``qvm-features``. The bind dirs "
"declaration must be done this way: ``qvm-features <VMNAME> custom-"
"persist.<ARBITRARY NAME> [PRE-CREATION SETTINGS]<PATH>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.rst:156
#: 4d66b3c2ab3544f8b5674f14207c7460
